WEBVTT

00:07.048 --> 00:08.049
Do you know where
they were headed?

00:08.049 --> 00:09.342
Could you tell?
That's him.

00:09.342 --> 00:11.511
The girl that
Bishop Paulsen saw.

00:11.511 --> 00:13.763
It was someone
else's daughter.

00:13.763 --> 00:15.223
You could've stopped it.

00:15.223 --> 00:16.641
He had repented.

00:16.641 --> 00:19.019
<i>Thought I was doing
the right thing.</i>

00:19.019 --> 00:20.520
Her mother passed tragically.

00:20.520 --> 00:22.022
Well, we're proud
to support the work

00:22.022 --> 00:24.524
you do for the White House
in any way we can, Mr. Tobler.

00:24.524 --> 00:26.109
You take care
of my Janice now.

00:26.109 --> 00:29.904
You need to get him talking
and let him lead us to her.

00:29.904 --> 00:32.866
<i>It is pure hell, Mary Ann,
not knowing where she is.</i>

00:32.866 --> 00:35.326
<i>Oh, just thinking about all
the awful things that might</i>

00:35.326 --> 00:37.078
<i>be happening to her out there.</i>

00:37.078 --> 00:40.582
You are an evil man.

00:40.582 --> 00:42.292
Evil.

01:37.514 --> 01:39.182
Anything you want.

01:41.559 --> 01:43.728
Yeah, I'll take a hot dog.

01:43.728 --> 01:45.146
A hot dog?

01:45.146 --> 01:47.440
Anything in the world,
and you wanna have a hot dog.

01:47.440 --> 01:49.234
Okay. Don't tell your mother.

01:49.234 --> 01:51.319
What are you gonna put on it?

02:01.913 --> 02:05.250
Now, you wait here,
and I'll be back in a jiff.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.710
All right?
- All right.

02:06.710 --> 02:08.169
All right.

02:26.312 --> 02:27.981
Hello? Brobergs.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.607
<i>- Hi, Mary Ann.</i>

02:31.026 --> 02:33.611
Hiya, B.

02:33.611 --> 02:35.697
It's nice to hear your voice.

02:35.697 --> 02:37.991
I think you'd be even happier
when you hear why I'm calling.

02:37.991 --> 02:40.160
Oh, is that right?

02:40.160 --> 02:45.206
A contact of mine spotted
Jan across state lines,

02:45.206 --> 02:47.459
a real surprising
location for her.

02:47.459 --> 02:48.752
<i>Why should I believe</i>

02:48.752 --> 02:50.337
<i>a single word
out of your mouth?</i>

02:50.337 --> 02:54.090
<i>You'll listen 'cause you'll
have nothing if you don't.</i>

02:54.090 --> 02:56.343
Now...

02:56.343 --> 03:00.430
I'll tell you everything,
but only in person,

03:00.430 --> 03:02.766
'cause I know these lines
can be tapped,

03:02.766 --> 03:05.185
and I don't want my words
being twisted against me.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.437
They're not tapped.

03:07.437 --> 03:09.230
<i>Oh, sure they are.</i>

03:09.230 --> 03:11.191
You've got a recording device
right there next to you

03:11.191 --> 03:13.360
in the kitchen.

03:13.360 --> 03:15.862
Did Gail tell you that?

03:15.862 --> 03:17.864
<i>You never mind that,
Mary Ann.</i>

03:17.864 --> 03:20.283
You just come in person.

03:20.283 --> 03:24.079
And you come alone,
no police, no Bob.

03:24.079 --> 03:25.663
<i>I've had about enough of him.</i>

03:25.663 --> 03:27.707
That's a lot of conditions.

03:27.707 --> 03:31.503
Well, I'm doing you a favor
telling you everything I know.

03:31.503 --> 03:34.214
And I need to feel like
there's a little trust.

03:34.214 --> 03:35.674
Of course, there is.

03:38.885 --> 03:41.388
What do you say we meet
at the Crossroads Cafe

03:41.388 --> 03:43.181
near Ogden City?

03:43.181 --> 03:45.934
Noon on Saturday.

03:45.934 --> 03:47.852
That's a week away.
Why not sooner?

03:47.852 --> 03:49.312
<i>Well, I'm busy.</i>

03:49.312 --> 03:51.439
I'm scouring the Earth
trying to find Jan.

03:51.439 --> 03:53.692
<i>You said you
knew where she was.</i>

03:53.692 --> 03:55.360
And I know you can't
leave the state

03:55.360 --> 03:56.528
because of your parole.

03:56.528 --> 03:58.154
<i>Mary Ann, Mary Ann,</i>

03:58.154 --> 04:00.198
the only thing
that matters to me

04:00.198 --> 04:02.200
is finding Jan.

04:02.200 --> 04:05.787
If that doesn't work for you,
then we don't have to meet.

04:13.628 --> 04:17.132
<i>Crossroads Cafe, Saturday.</i>

05:17.942 --> 05:19.611
Give me strength.

05:21.613 --> 05:23.490
Give me strength.

05:26.451 --> 05:28.119
Give me--
- Janice?

05:29.913 --> 05:31.706
Are you OK?

05:34.000 --> 05:36.795
I heard you
the last few nights.

05:36.795 --> 05:38.505
And...

05:38.505 --> 05:41.591
it sounded like
you were crying.

05:41.591 --> 05:43.677
I wasn't crying.

05:45.428 --> 05:47.055
You miss Lebanon?

05:51.101 --> 05:53.687
I miss where I'm from
before that.

05:57.273 --> 05:59.401
And I miss my family.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.782
I used to act in all
the school plays.

06:07.701 --> 06:09.494
So I miss that.

06:14.624 --> 06:18.545
There's this play
at the boys' school.

06:20.130 --> 06:24.592
I wanted to audition,
but I was too shy to go alone.

06:29.514 --> 06:32.434
It's "As You Like It"
by Shakespeare.

06:34.728 --> 06:36.855
I can't talk to boys.

06:36.855 --> 06:38.565
Says who?

06:38.565 --> 06:40.191
We're at boarding school.

06:46.072 --> 06:48.158
Beautiful car.

06:48.158 --> 06:49.617
How you doin'?

06:51.995 --> 06:53.580
Hey.

06:53.580 --> 06:55.623
Hey, can I help you?

06:55.623 --> 06:58.418
<i>- * Some people run ♪</i>

06:58.418 --> 06:59.919
What the hell are you doing?

06:59.919 --> 07:02.422
<i>- * Some people crawl ♪</i>

07:02.422 --> 07:03.631
Whew.

07:05.759 --> 07:07.802
Thanks for holding this for me.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.722
Bob, you know you can
count on me

07:10.722 --> 07:12.349
when you're down on your luck,
but that don't mean

07:12.349 --> 07:14.601
you can store guns
on my lot now.

07:16.019 --> 07:18.229
Well...

07:18.229 --> 07:20.106
I asked you before
if I could store it here.

07:20.106 --> 07:21.274
You said yes.

07:21.274 --> 07:23.276
I don't remember that.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.903
Maybe you're losing it, Joe.

07:24.903 --> 07:27.572
I got the FBI
calling me again,

07:27.572 --> 07:29.908
asking if I know where Jan is.

07:29.908 --> 07:30.992
Yeah.

07:32.577 --> 07:33.912
You know, as a matter of fact--

07:33.912 --> 07:35.622
- I don't wanna know.
- No, no, no, no.

07:35.622 --> 07:36.998
No. Hey, hey, hey, hey.

07:36.998 --> 07:38.541
Joe. Joe.

07:38.541 --> 07:41.294
There's something I've been
meaning to talk to you about.

07:41.294 --> 07:43.088
I wanted to say thank you.

07:44.839 --> 07:47.967
For when you turned me
and Jan in,

07:47.967 --> 07:49.219
in Mexico.

07:50.512 --> 07:52.847
At the time I was angry.

07:54.015 --> 07:56.810
In the end, I'm just grateful,
you know?

07:56.810 --> 07:59.729
Because we're in a much better
place now.

07:59.729 --> 08:02.816
All those obstacles,
I think they brought us closer.

08:02.816 --> 08:05.860
You know, I feel like we really
know each other now

08:05.860 --> 08:07.821
as lovers

08:07.821 --> 08:10.865
and also as friends, you know?

08:10.865 --> 08:12.075
As--

08:13.368 --> 08:15.036
As partners.

08:15.036 --> 08:17.956
Bob, you get that girl
pregnant, you're screwed.

08:17.956 --> 08:20.583
Well, it's hardly an issue.

08:20.583 --> 08:22.669
I don't know where
she even is.

08:25.880 --> 08:29.592
Anyway, she ain't even
got her period yet, so--

08:33.013 --> 08:35.306
It's always good
seeing you, Joe.

08:39.185 --> 08:42.814
Hey, find somewhere else
to store your shit, Bob.

08:42.814 --> 08:45.108
I don't want nothing
to do with this.

08:45.108 --> 08:46.234
I'm done.

08:46.234 --> 08:49.195
Sure thing, toughie.
Whatever you say.

09:07.380 --> 09:08.882
Mary Ann.

09:08.882 --> 09:10.717
Detective George Shail,
Ogden Police.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.218
Sorry for the short notice.

09:12.218 --> 09:13.887
I appreciate you coming down.
- Of course.

09:13.887 --> 09:15.430
I'll do anything to help.

09:15.430 --> 09:17.015
We've been watching Berchtold

09:17.015 --> 09:18.850
since Agent Welsh put him
on our radar.

09:18.850 --> 09:22.354
A lot of us have
young children, so--

09:22.354 --> 09:24.230
What we need you to do

09:24.230 --> 09:27.150
is tell us if this is the girl
you saw with him.

09:33.698 --> 09:35.909
- Yes, that's her.
- All right.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.244
We'll show her a photo of Jan.

09:39.621 --> 09:41.122
Officer Jensen?

09:48.880 --> 09:52.801
Carly, do you
recognize this girl?

10:03.645 --> 10:04.854
Ma'am, what is your relationship

10:04.854 --> 10:06.439
to Robert Berchtold?

10:06.439 --> 10:08.525
Uh, is--

10:08.525 --> 10:10.735
is this because
of the Brobergs?

10:10.735 --> 10:14.489
Because I know all
about them, you know?

10:14.489 --> 10:18.660
They will not rest until his
life is ruined,

10:18.660 --> 10:20.954
no matter how many stories
they tell.

10:20.954 --> 10:22.831
It's really something.

10:24.582 --> 10:27.002
You know...

10:27.002 --> 10:29.504
Bob has his struggles.

10:29.504 --> 10:31.798
But he's a good man.

10:31.798 --> 10:33.717
He's always there
when I need him.

10:33.717 --> 10:35.927
He's helped me
in countless ways.

10:35.927 --> 10:40.306
And he's just been a complete
angel with my Carly.

10:40.306 --> 10:43.601
We just need to know what
your relationship is to him--

10:43.601 --> 10:46.730
friend, boyfriend?

10:48.106 --> 10:50.025
He's like a family member.

10:51.651 --> 10:53.653
What do you think
about Bob, honey?

10:53.653 --> 10:55.113
He's so much fun.

10:55.113 --> 10:57.824
We do everything together.

10:57.824 --> 10:59.659
He's my best friend.

11:36.780 --> 11:38.948
Thanks for coming right over.

11:38.948 --> 11:42.744
I am really not supposed
to be here right now.

11:43.620 --> 11:48.249
Mary Ann, you cannot
go see Berchtold by yourself.

11:50.085 --> 11:52.212
He's worried about
being recorded.

11:52.212 --> 11:54.714
If I go in person,
maybe he'll actually

11:54.714 --> 11:56.049
give us something we can use.

11:56.049 --> 11:57.384
The only thing that
he is worried about

11:57.384 --> 11:59.052
is getting a legal marriage
on the books

11:59.052 --> 12:01.054
to protect himself
from prosecution.

12:01.054 --> 12:02.931
He needs your consent.

12:02.931 --> 12:05.183
If you go and meet
him in person,

12:05.183 --> 12:07.644
he may use force to try to
get you to sign those papers.

12:07.644 --> 12:09.771
- It's a public place.
- Oh, Mary Ann, that's--

12:09.771 --> 12:12.482
My daughter is out there.

12:15.777 --> 12:17.612
I can't just wait.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.253
It's a personal piece.

12:35.964 --> 12:37.841
If you must go, take it.

12:46.599 --> 12:49.602
Mary Ann, it's for protection.

12:49.602 --> 12:52.731
Please, don't just shoot him.

13:09.122 --> 13:11.583
Hey there, movie star.

13:11.583 --> 13:13.084
Come on.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.630
Hi.

13:24.804 --> 13:26.765
OK, you ready?

13:26.765 --> 13:28.183
Come on.

13:49.371 --> 13:52.415
It's so nice to have
the whole day to ourselves.

13:56.544 --> 13:58.505
So how you doin', Dolly?

13:59.881 --> 14:01.675
I'm good.

14:01.675 --> 14:04.177
Oh, I get it.

14:04.177 --> 14:07.055
Well, we all get
the blues sometimes,

14:07.055 --> 14:08.765
even yours truly,

14:08.765 --> 14:10.684
shocking as that may be
to hear.

14:10.684 --> 14:12.852
But it's a beautiful day.

14:12.852 --> 14:15.647
So what are we gonna do next?

14:15.647 --> 14:20.068
Go to the Chinese Theater again
or Hollywood Wax Museum?

14:21.277 --> 14:24.406
Uh, I--I don't really
mind either.

14:24.406 --> 14:26.116
You can pick.

14:26.116 --> 14:28.326
What's with you? Huh?

14:31.079 --> 14:33.039
It's not the wrong time
of the month, is it?

14:34.874 --> 14:38.461
I still haven't gotten it,
if that's what you're asking.

14:38.461 --> 14:41.923
Good.

14:43.091 --> 14:45.260
Zeda and Zethra were concerned.

14:45.260 --> 14:46.469
So--

14:47.637 --> 14:50.765
They asked you about that?
How come?

14:50.765 --> 14:55.186
Well, if you don't get
your human period, then...

14:55.186 --> 14:57.564
you can't be pregnant.
- Oh.

14:57.564 --> 15:00.567
I haven't had one this entire
time and I'm not pregnant.

15:00.567 --> 15:03.028
Oh, exactly.

15:03.028 --> 15:04.404
Exactly what?

15:04.404 --> 15:06.031
Is that right for
a half-human like me?

15:06.031 --> 15:07.532
Uh, you know,

15:07.532 --> 15:10.160
biology's a whole other
ball game on their planet.

15:10.160 --> 15:12.912
So, you know,
I'm thinking wax museum.

15:12.912 --> 15:15.290
How do you know stuff
about biology on their planet?

15:15.290 --> 15:17.625
Zeda and Zethra talk
to me all the time.

15:17.625 --> 15:19.169
All the time?
When did that start?

15:19.169 --> 15:21.087
You know what?

15:21.087 --> 15:23.381
Dolly, I don't tell you
about all this stuff

15:23.381 --> 15:25.091
because it's traumatizing,
OK, and I don't

15:25.091 --> 15:27.302
want to burden you with it.

15:27.302 --> 15:29.387
So I bear it on my own.

15:30.555 --> 15:31.931
OK?

15:31.931 --> 15:34.309
- OK.
- OK.

15:36.728 --> 15:38.480
And don't bite your nails.

15:38.480 --> 15:40.482
You'll bite them
down to nothing.

15:42.984 --> 15:45.487
How about another
driving lesson, huh?

15:45.487 --> 15:46.654
Yeah, all right.

15:46.654 --> 15:48.406
Here we go.

15:49.699 --> 15:53.620
Uh-huh. Stay to the right,
stay to the right.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.872
Oh, that is great, Dolly.

15:55.872 --> 15:57.624
That is great.
You're a natural.

16:00.251 --> 16:02.087
This is a pretty neighborhood.

16:02.087 --> 16:03.463
Yeah.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.382
It looks different now
that I'm having fun.

16:07.509 --> 16:09.552
What do you mean different?

16:09.552 --> 16:11.012
Different from when?

16:12.180 --> 16:16.184
Oh, I don't know
what I'm talking about.

16:19.229 --> 16:21.815
When have you been
here before?

16:21.815 --> 16:24.943
Um, I--

16:24.943 --> 16:27.028
it wasn't a big deal.

16:27.028 --> 16:28.780
It was just an audition
for a play.

16:28.780 --> 16:30.198
A play?

16:32.325 --> 16:33.952
What kind of play?

16:33.952 --> 16:35.537
Just a school one.

16:36.788 --> 16:38.289
Shakespeare.

16:39.582 --> 16:41.793
So why wasn't
it on campus then?

16:43.962 --> 16:47.382
It was at a different school.

16:49.592 --> 16:51.386
A boys' school?

16:53.388 --> 16:54.848
Are you telling
me you auditioned

16:54.848 --> 16:56.391
for a play at a boys' school?

16:56.391 --> 16:58.351
I didn't even talk
to any of the boys.

16:58.351 --> 16:59.853
You expect me
to believe that?

16:59.853 --> 17:01.021
Well, B, it's true.

17:01.021 --> 17:02.230
Were you even
gonna tell me?

17:02.230 --> 17:03.606
You were at a school
with boys and men,

17:03.606 --> 17:04.566
and you think that's OK?

17:04.566 --> 17:05.775
You think it's OK
for the mission?

17:05.775 --> 17:07.986
I wasn't even the
one who wanted to go.

17:07.986 --> 17:10.405
You know, when you lie,
you don't just hurt me.

17:10.405 --> 17:12.907
You hurt your own soul.

17:12.907 --> 17:14.367
Stay to the right.

17:14.367 --> 17:16.703
And worst of all,
you hurt the mission.

17:16.703 --> 17:19.664
Do you even care about
the mission at all?

17:19.664 --> 17:21.708
Of course, I do.

17:21.708 --> 17:24.669
You know it's all that I think
about all day and all night.

17:24.669 --> 17:26.171
I can't even sleep.

17:26.171 --> 17:27.380
I'm doing everything
that they're asking--

17:27.380 --> 17:28.798
Hey, Dolly!

17:32.302 --> 17:35.138
<i>♪ When the deep purple
falls ♪</i>

17:35.138 --> 17:37.390
<i>♪ Over sleepy garden walls ♪</i>

17:37.390 --> 17:39.559
<i>♪ Sleepy garden walls ♪</i>

17:39.559 --> 17:42.103
<i>♪ And stars begin
to twinkle ♪</i>

17:48.276 --> 17:50.612
<i>♪ In the midst of a memory ♪</i>

17:54.032 --> 17:55.283
I think that's hard.

17:55.283 --> 17:58.328
We're all OK.

17:58.328 --> 18:01.623
OK, well, you're [instinct].
- Yes, [indistinct].

18:01.623 --> 18:03.208
OK. Take care.

18:05.960 --> 18:08.630
Scoot over.
Move over.

18:24.896 --> 18:26.606
Do you think I have
to go to the hospital?

18:26.606 --> 18:28.400
No, I don't think you need
to go to the hospital.

18:28.400 --> 18:30.193
It's a bump on the noggin.

18:30.193 --> 18:32.904
And even if it was worse,
I couldn't take you.

18:32.904 --> 18:34.948
You know that, right?

18:34.948 --> 18:36.324
I just--

18:36.324 --> 18:37.742
I feel kinda dizzy.

18:37.742 --> 18:41.079
Well, thanks to Mary Ann
and Bob's treachery,

18:41.079 --> 18:42.414
we're not even safe
where we are.

18:42.414 --> 18:45.333
If a cop had driven by--

18:45.333 --> 18:47.961
You know, thanks
to your parents and my parole,

18:47.961 --> 18:49.629
I can't leave Utah.

18:49.629 --> 18:53.383
So a hospital record
in the state of California,

18:53.383 --> 18:55.135
that sends me right back
to jail.

18:55.135 --> 18:56.803
And then where would we be?

18:56.803 --> 18:58.346
And I told you to watch
the road, didn't I?

18:58.346 --> 19:00.306
I told you to watch the road!

19:12.861 --> 19:14.738
And what if I'd lost you?

19:18.533 --> 19:20.535
I'm really sorry.

19:22.620 --> 19:24.748
I didn't mean to upset you.

19:24.748 --> 19:27.834
You're my angel
on this Earth, Dolly.

19:27.834 --> 19:30.128
Here you are, hurt,
and you're worried about me.

19:37.385 --> 19:39.721
You know, I didn't wanna
have to tell you this,

19:39.721 --> 19:42.098
but...

19:42.098 --> 19:44.267
the reason that Zeda and Zethra
have been contacting me

19:44.267 --> 19:45.727
is 'cause they're angry
with you.

19:45.727 --> 19:47.729
They said that?

19:47.729 --> 19:49.522
Yeah, they're upset
that we're not married yet.

19:49.522 --> 19:51.983
And they think that you're
not trying hard enough.

19:51.983 --> 19:53.693
But I am. I am trying. I--

19:53.693 --> 19:55.070
They've started to talk
about what to do

19:55.070 --> 19:56.654
because you've lost faith.

19:56.654 --> 19:58.323
And they may not wait
till you're 16.

19:58.323 --> 19:59.574
They may take Susan
and make her

19:59.574 --> 20:01.201
take your place right now.

20:01.201 --> 20:03.578
They said that?

20:03.578 --> 20:06.956
And the scary thing is,
she's so small.

20:09.417 --> 20:12.921
She's so small having a baby
could kill her.

20:19.010 --> 20:21.388
Because they've been clear
from the start,

20:21.388 --> 20:24.391
if it falls to Susan,

20:24.391 --> 20:27.185
you'll only have yourself
to blame.

20:31.773 --> 20:37.070
Now, that is why
we have to get married.

20:37.070 --> 20:39.322
All right?

20:39.322 --> 20:40.865
When this trip is over,
I'm going to get

20:40.865 --> 20:42.784
those last ducks in a row
to make sure that happens.

20:42.784 --> 20:46.037
But you're with me on this,
right, completely?

20:46.037 --> 20:48.915
No distractions, no slacking.

20:48.915 --> 20:50.417
Total focus.

